==When Used==
*''Without a [[Your Mystical Bookshelf|mystical bookshelf]]'':
{{useitem|text=You take the Tome to your campsite, and a strange shimmering bookshelf appears near your dwelling. You put the Tome on it.}}

*''With a [[Your Mystical Bookshelf|mystical bookshelf]] without a Tome of Snowcone Summoning on it'':
{{useitem|text=You place the Tome carefully on the bookshelf in your campsite.}}

*''With a Tome of Snowcone Summoning already on the [[Your Mystical Bookshelf|mystical bookshelf]]'':
{{useitem|text=You've already got a copy of that Tome on your bookshelf.}}

==Notes==
{{IotM Description|date=January 2006|desc=When used, gives you a skill that lets you summon three delicious [[snowcones]] per day. Six exciting flavors!}}
{{Mystic Book|skill=Summon Snowcones}}
*Fortunately, the Tome does not let you summon the [[yellow snowcone]].
*According to an Announcement on February 21, 2006, "Tomes of snowcone summoning now mark you no-delete."
*This was the first Mr. Store item to grant you a skill.
*First prize in [[The Raffle House]] on January 30, 2008.

==References==
*The description imitates the form of the [[Wikipedia:Mentat#The Mentat Mantra|Mentat Mantra]] from David Lynch's movie adaptation of [[Wikipedia:Frank Herbert|Frank Herbert]]'s novel ''[[Wikipedia:Dune (novel)|Dune]]'':  "It is by will alone I set my mind in motion.  It is by the juice of Sapho that thoughts acquire speed, the lips acquire stains, the stains become a warning.  It is by will alone I set my mind in motion."

